Status asthmaticus is recognized as a common cause of morbidity in children in the United States.

 In recent years, hospitalization rates have reached an all time high.

 This study will evaluate the safety, tolerability and clinical benefit of adding Noninvasive Positive Pressure Ventilation (NPPV)to regular care in children with moderate to moderately severe status asthmaticus.

